{
  "stem": "17761.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And on the shore, the members of the Haganah that organized that, with the Bulgarian officers and non-Jewish officer, singing together the 'Hatikvah.' That is a picture I'll never forget.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But we didn't go too far.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We just went a little bit in the Black Sea outside of the territorial waters of the Bulgaria, because the Bulgarians didn't want-- they had-- they were afraid that the British are going to intervene.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So we wanted to be outside of their territories.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But we had to wait a second ship that had to be loaded.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they didn't manage to reach before Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So they had to stop in the field somewhere over Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And only Motza'ei Yom Kippur they came in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they packed up this other little ship.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was about 1,600 Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And so we were two ships on the Black Sea, sailing for-- for Eretz Israel, and 4,000 people in them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "If you would have seen the ships-- it was the 'In-tri-pid,' or something like this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There was a kind of an-- one was an icebreaker, but OK.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we started to sail together until-- by the way, next day, we all took all of our documents that we had.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We tore them up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We threw it into the Black Sea.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we are now new people, newborn people, all of us-- free people going to Eretz Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And until we came to Turkey, we had to go through the Bosphorus, and then to-- through the Marmara Sea, and we came to the Dardanelles.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And as we crossed the Dardanelles into the Mediterranean, the-- the Aegean Sea to the Mediterranean, there was already a British destroyer waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "British hospitality is renowned, so they sent a destroyer to greet us.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
